claim.claim-text:
1. A method of fabricating a transistor, comprising:
forming a channel region in a semiconductor substrate;
forming a bottom semiconductor material directly over the channel region of the semiconductor substrate and doping the bottom semiconductor material;
forming an intrinsic semiconductor material over the bottom semiconductor material; and
forming a top semiconductor material over the intrinsic semiconductor material and doping the top semiconductor material.

4. A method of fabricating a transistor, comprising:
forming a channel region in a semiconductor substrate;
forming a bottom semiconductor material directly on the semiconductor substrate and doping the bottom semiconductor material;
forming an intrinsic semiconductor material over the bottom semiconductor material;
forming a top semiconductor material over the intrinsic semiconductor material and doping the top semiconductor material; and
forming a first protective material directly on the bottom semiconductor material, and forming a second protective material directly on the intrinsic semiconductor material.

8. A method of fabricating a transistor, comprising
forming a channel region in a semiconductor substrate;
forming an intrinsic semiconductor material over the channel region;
forming a top semiconductor material over the intrinsic semiconductor material, and doping the top semiconductor material; and
forming a first protective material between the intrinsic semiconductor material and the top semiconductor material.
